image_analysis.description: A photograph taken from a doorway looking into a room or hallway. In the center of the frame is a life-sized statue of a Terracotta Warrior, viewed from the back and side. The statue is dark gray/black with a weathered texture. To the left, a large vertical painting is visible on the wall, depicting a nude figure with certain areas redacted by black boxes. The room has blue patterned carpeting and beige/tan walls. A circular light fixture is mounted on the ceiling. The photograph is framed by the white door jambs of the doorway from which it was taken.
image_analysis.layout: Interior room shot through a doorway.

document_metadata.subject: Interior photograph of a residence featuring a Terracotta Warrior statue and artwork

notes: The photograph contains a Bates stamp 'EFTA00001049' in the bottom right corner, indicating it is part of a legal or investigative production. The painting on the wall has been censored with black boxes.
